  <h1>LG Dryer Door Won't Close - Expert Repair Service Los Angeles</h1>
  <p>When your LG dryer door won't close properly, clothes can't dry and your laundry routine stops dead. Our technicians diagnose door latch problems, hinge issues, and alignment failures across Los Angeles County. Call (323) 990-7550 for same-day repair service.</p>

<h2>Warning Signs Your LG Dryer Door Needs Professional Repair</h2>
<p>The most obvious sign is when the door simply won't stay closed during operation, but there are subtler symptoms our techs see regularly in Pasadena and Burbank homes. If you're hearing clicking sounds when trying to close the door, the latch mechanism is likely worn or misaligned.</p>
<figure class="article-img article-img--square">
  <img src="/images/symptoms/lg-dryer-door-wont-close-latch-new.webp"
       alt="Worn LG dryer door latch assembly — damaged mechanism causing door failure"
       width="600" height="600" loading="lazy" />
  <figcaption>Worn latch assembly — the plastic catch loses its
  spring tension over time and stops engaging the door strike</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>We also get calls when doors close but the dryer won't start - this usually means the door switch isn't engaging properly with the latch assembly. Sometimes the door appears closed but pops open mid-cycle, which creates a safety hazard and prevents proper drying. Visual inspection reveals other red flags: gaps around the door seal, the door handle feeling loose or wobbly, or the door sitting crooked when closed.</p>
<figure class="article-img">
  <img src="/images/symptoms/lg-dryer-door-wont-close-gap-new.webp"
       alt="LG dryer door not closing properly — visible gap around door seal"
       width="800" height="600" loading="lazy" />
  <figcaption>Visible gap when door is closed — hot air escapes
  every cycle, clothes stay damp and thermal fuse fails early</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>Nine times out of ten, these issues stem from worn door hinges, a damaged latch assembly, or the door strike becoming loose over time. Don't ignore intermittent problems - they typically worsen quickly and can damage other components like the <a href="/repairs/lg-dryer-thermal-fuse-replacement/">thermal fuse</a> when doors don't seal properly during operation.</p>
<h3>Critical Safety Symptoms</h3>
<p>If your LG dryer door flies open during operation, stop using the unit immediately. This creates serious safety risks including potential burns from hot air and damaged clothing from the spinning drum. Our technicians in Beverly Hills frequently see cases where continued operation with a faulty door damages the door switch or control board, turning a simple latch repair into a much more expensive fix.</p>
<h2>Our Professional LG Dryer Door Repair Process</h2>
<p>When you call (323) 990-7550, we schedule same-day service and arrive with diagnostic tools to identify the exact problem. The first thing we check is whether the issue is mechanical (hinges, latch assembly) or electrical (door switch, wiring connections). Our technician removes the door to inspect hinge pins and bushings, then tests the latch mechanism and door strike alignment. We carry common LG door components on our trucks, so most repairs complete in one visit. For DLGX and DLEX series models, we often find the door strike assembly needs adjustment or replacement - a job that takes about 45 minutes including testing. If the door hinges are worn, we replace both hinges simultaneously to prevent future alignment problems.</p>
