  what else you fix</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>After repairs, we run a complete test cycle to verify the door seals properly and the safety interlock functions correctly. Our 85% first-visit fix rate means most customers in Glendale and Torrance get their dryer working the same day we arrive.</p>
<h3>Diagnostic Testing Protocol</h3>
<p>Our technicians follow a systematic approach: visual inspection of door alignment, manual testing of latch engagement, electrical testing of door switch operation, and checking for worn components. We document all findings and explain exactly what needs repair before starting any work, ensuring you understand the problem and solution.</p>
<h2>Why Professional Repair Beats DIY for LG Dryer Doors</h2>
<p>Door repairs involve precise alignment and electrical safety that require specialized tools and experience. We see homeowners in Santa Monica who attempted DIY repairs and ended up with doors that close but don't seal properly, leading to inefficient drying and potential <a href="/symptoms/lg-dryer-not-heating/">heating problems</a>. The door strike assembly must be positioned within millimeters for proper latch engagement - something that's difficult without proper alignment tools. Electrical connections to the door switch involve live circuits that pose shock risks if handled incorrectly. Our technicians carry model-specific hinges and latch assemblies, while DIY repairs often use generic parts that don't fit properly or last as long. Safety is another major concern: incorrectly installed door components can fail during operation, potentially causing injury or property damage. Professional repair also comes with our 1-year warranty on parts and labor, protecting your investment. Most importantly, we understand the relationship between door problems and other dryer issues - a door that doesn't seal can cause the unit to overheat, potentially damaging expensive components like the control board or <a href="/repairs/lg-dryer-heating-element-replacement/">heating element</a>.</p>
<h3>Common DIY Mistakes We Fix</h3>
<p>The most frequent DIY error we encounter is over-tightening hinge screws, which strips the mounting holes and requires cabinet repair. We also see doors installed with incorrect hinge orientation, causing binding and premature wear. Electrical mistakes include wrong wire connections that can damage the control board - a much more expensive repair than the original door problem.</p>
<h2>LG Dryer Door Repair Cost vs Replacement Analysis</h2>
<p>Most LG dryer door repairs range from $320-380 including parts and labor, while a new dryer costs $800-1500 depending on features and capacity. The exact cost depends on which components need replacement and your dryer model. Door latch assemblies typically run $45-75, while hinge sets cost $35-60 for genuine LG parts. Labor accounts for the majority of the service cost due to the precision required for proper alignment and testing. Our service call fee gets waived when you proceed with repairs, and we price parts transparently - you can verify component costs on supplier websites. For premium LG models in Calabasas and Malibu homes, parts may cost more due to specialized components, but repair still costs far less than replacement. Consider that a 3-5 year old LG dryer with a door problem is worth repairing, while units over 8 years old might benefit from replacement depending on overall condition. We provide honest recommendations based on your specific situation. Our flexible pricing policy means if we source parts at better prices or have components in our warehouse at old pricing, those savings get passed directly to you.</p>
<h3>When Replacement Makes More Sense</h3>
<p>If your LG dryer is over 10 years old and needs multiple repairs beyond just the door, replacement might be more economical. We'll honestly assess the overall condition and help you make the best financial decision. However, for most door issues on units under 8 years old, professional repair is the smart choice.</p>

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<h3>How long does LG dryer door repair take?</h3>
<p>Most door repairs take 45-90 minutes depending on the specific problem. Simple latch adjustments are quicker, while hinge replacement takes longer due to precision alignment requirements.</p>
<h3>Can I still use my dryer if the door won't stay closed?</h3>
<p>Never operate a dryer with a door that won't stay closed properly. This creates safety hazards and can damage other components when hot air escapes during operation.</p>
<h3>What causes LG dryer doors to stop closing properly?</h3>
<p>The most common causes are worn hinge pins, damaged latch assemblies, or misaligned door strikes. Heavy use over time causes these components to wear and lose proper alignment.</p>
<h3>Do you stock LG dryer door parts on your service trucks?</h3>
<p>Yes, we carry the most common door components for popular LG models including DLGX and DLEX series. This allows us to complete most repairs in one visit with genuine OEM parts.</p>
